1. Definitions
User or You means any natural person, legal person or other organisation accessing or using the Services under these terms and conditions.
Access or accessing means any behaviour including but not limited to downloading, installing, applying, accessing, visiting, or using the Services by any other means wherein the User interacts, benefits, or acquires information from the Services.
Force Majeure shall mean forces beyond the reasonable control of any Party, including, without limitation, fire, flood, acts of God, pandemic, labour disputes, accidents, acts of war or terrorism, civil disobedience, interruptions of transportation or communications and supply shortages.
Use or using means any time a User, directly or indirectly, does or attempts to access, interact with, display, view, print or copy from the Services, transmit, receive information, or exchange data or communicates with the Services, or in any way utilises, benefits, takes advantage of, or interacts with any function, product, or feature of the Services.
Account means one or more account(s) held in the name of the User with Sahm Capital for the purposes of accessing to or using the Services.
2. Register for an Account
The User may open an Account on the Sahm Capital application, client software or website in order to use certain areas and features of the Services.  When registering for an Account, the User expressly agrees to provide a valid personal mobile phone number, type in the instant valid verification code for authentication and create a unique password.  Upon the completion of the same, the User will have a registered Account with Sahm Capital.
Once the User has registered for an Account, it shall be deemed that the User has agreed to authorise Sahm Capital to send to the mobile phone number of the User a variety of text messages, including but not limited to, account security prompt messages, mobile phone log-in verification code and password modification prompt message.
The User further agrees to:
a. ensure that the information provided is accurate, truthful, current, and complete.
b. maintains and promptly update the Account information upon the occurrence of any changes to the same.
c. maintains the security of the Account by protecting its password and restricting its access; d) be the sole user of the Account and password and not to permit another to access the Account.
e. promptly notifies Sahm Capital in writing if it is suspected that an unauthorised individual has accessed the Account or upon the occurrence of a security breach related to the Services; and
l. takes full responsibility for all activities that occur under the Account and accept all risks of any authorised or unauthorised access and assume all the consequences and liabilities incurred from the failure of the User to comply with the terms and conditions of the Agreement. Sahm Capital shall not assume any responsibility in respect of the same.
A successful login into the Account of the User with the password of the User shall automatically be deemed to have been logged in by the User. The User shall bear all the relevant liabilities in relation to the Account of the User. If the Account and password is illegally used, Sahm Capital shall have the right to suspend or cease the User qualification of the said account without assuming any liabilities and report such unauthorised access to the relevant authority in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.
3. User Conduct and Management
User Conduct Permission
Use of Information
All market information available on the website, desktop, and mobile APP of Sahm Capital (the Information) is provided by third parties, including but not limited to the Saudi Arabian Stock Exchange (Tadawul or the Saudi Exchange), New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Exchange or other exchanges and its authorised information providers (collectively, the Exchanges or each one as the Exchange).  The User understands that each Exchange endeavours to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the Information provided but does not guarantee its accuracy and reliability and accepts no liability (whether in tort or contract or otherwise) for any loss or damage arising from any inaccuracies or omissions or from any decision, action or non-action based on or in reliance upon Information contained in its website or published by it.
The User shall proceed with caution when evaluating and using the accuracy of the price quotes, charts, comments, purchase or other information on the website, desktop and mobile APP of Sahm Capital by the User and the User shall be solely liable for all losses incurred from the use of the Information.
By accessing or using the Saudi Exchange Delayed Information, which shall be any Information that is delayed at least fifteen (15) minutes from the time of original dissemination, the User hereby understand and agrees that:
a. the Saudi Exchange and its authorised information providers reserve all Intellectual Property Rights to the Information.
b. the Saudi Exchange and its authorised information providers accept no liability whatsoever for the display of the Information or any losses or claims arising from use of the Information.
c. Information is for the personal use of the User and the User may not re-distribute or re-publish such Information to any third party without the express written permission of the Saudi Exchange.
d. the User shall have no right to use Information in automated trading applications, to create derived data or to process Information, with or without other data, for the purpose of creating indices, or to license a third party to create indices, without the prior written permission of the Saudi Exchange.
e. the User shall have no right to use Information to create, price or benchmark any financial product(s), or to license any third party to do so, without the prior written permission of the Saudi Exchange.
f. the Saudi Exchange may suspend or terminate receipt of Information by any party if the Saudi Exchange has reason to believe that the Information is being misused or misrepresented; and
g. nothing contained in the Agreement shall permit the User to assume that Sahm Capital has authorised the User or any third party to misuse, distribute or publish the Information.
Use of interactive areas
The Services include interactive areas where the User along with other users may post, download, store or transmit content, messages, materials, data, information, text, music, sound, photos, videos, graphics or other items or materials on the Services (collectively, User Content) or interact with other Users. The User may use the Services for non-commercial purposes and post, download, store or transmit User Content in accordance with the Agreement. Sahm Capital makes no warranties or representations as to the User Content and has no responsibility or liability with respect to any communications, transactions, interactions, disputes, or any relations whatsoever between the User and other users. The User understands and acknowledges that Sahm Capital cannot and does not endorse or verify any information, conduct or content posted on the interactive areas nor does it conduct any background searches or verifications of users.
The User expressly agrees that the use of the Services by the User is at the risk of the User and the sole responsibility of the User when using the Services and such interactive areas. Sahm Capital may, in its sole discretion may refuse, remove, or delete any User Content without notice and subject to any requirements or notices issued by the Saudi Arabian Capital Market Authority (the CMA) to remove or delete the same. If the User becomes aware of any use of the Services or User Content that violates the terms of the Agreement, the User should notify Sahm Capital immediately by using the reporting tools provided via the Services.
User Conduct Restriction
To use the Services, the User agrees to abide by the terms of the Agreement with respect to User Conduct Restriction and undertakes:
a. to comply with the applicable laws, regulations, rules, international conventions, and the terms as applicable to the Services and the Agreement.
b. not to use the Services for any illegal purpose or by any illegal method, including promoting or encouraging any illegal activity.
c. not to conduct any activity that is illegal or infringes the rights and interests of any third party, including without limitation, intellectual property, privacy, publicity, or contractual rights.
d. not to use the Services in any manner that could interfere with, disrupt, negatively affect, or inhibit other users from fully utilising the Services or that could damage, disable, overburden, or impair the functioning of the Services in any manner.
e. not to publish, transmit or disseminate any User Content that:
1. is unlawful, libellous, defamatory, harassing, threatening, invasive of privacy or publicity rights, or that would otherwise create liability or violate any applicable laws and regulations.
2. contains nudity, sexually explicit content or is otherwise obscene, pornographic, indecent, lewd, suggestive, or sexually exploitative of minors.
3. may disparage any ethnic, racial, or religious group by stereotypical depiction or is otherwise abusive or inflammatory.
4. contains offensive language or images or is otherwise objectionable.
5. incites violence or characterises violence as acceptable, glamorous, or desirable.
6. contains unsolicited promotions, political campaigning, advertising, or solicitations, without the prior written consent of Sahm Capital which shall be given or withheld in its sole discretion.
7. contains private or personal information about another person unless such person has agreed in writing to the disclosure of such information.
8. contains viruses, corrupted data or other harmful, disruptive, or destructive file viruses, cancel bots, Trojan horses, harmful code, flood pings, denial-of-service attacks, packet or IP spoofing, forged routing or electronic mail address information or similar methods or technology.
9. may infringe any patent, trademark, trade secret, copyright or other intellectual or proprietary right of any party.
10 would constitute, encourage, or provide instructions for a criminal offense or violate the rights of any third party.
11. carry out, abet, or assist any other person to conduct the above or other behaviours that is prohibited by law.
12 is against the teachings of Islam or the Shariah.
13. is culturally sensitive and against the norms of the Saudi Arabian society or history (collectively, the Undertaking).
f. In the event that the User violates the Undertaking, Sahm Capital shall have the right to immediately terminate or suspend the Services by cutting off the transmitted content, saving the transmission records, closing the Account or deleting the link to the infringing material, and shall report the same to the competent supervision authority in line with the rules and regulations in place in Saudi Arabia, including but not limited to the CMA.
User Content License
The User shall own all User Content posted by the User on the interactive areas in respect of the Services. By posting User Content onto the interactive areas, the User hereby expressly grants Sahm Capital a perpetual, worldwide, irrevocable, non-exclusive, royalty-free and fully sublicensable license to use, reproduce, display, perform, adapt, modify, create derivative works from, distribute, have distributed and promote such User Content in any form, in all platforms now known or hereinafter created to administer, operate, develop and otherwise provide the Services.
The User represents and warrants that:
a. the User owns and controls all rights to the User Content posted by the User or otherwise has rights to post such User Content to the Services.
b. the User Content is accurate, non-confidential, not misleading, or harmful in any manner.
c. the use and posting of the User Content does not violate the terms of the Agreement, the applicable laws or rules and will not violate any rights of or cause injury to any person or entity. Where User Content contains personal data about the User, our Privacy Policy will apply. By posting User Content pertaining to the User, the User represents that the User has read and understands the Privacy Policy and acknowledges that Sahm Capital has the right to use and share any such data posted on the interactive areas at its sole discretion and in line with the applicable rules and regulations.
