In using Sahm Capital Services, the User may have access to products or services provided by third parties (the Third-Party Service), either directly on the Sahm Capital Services platform or through links to third-party websites, and in some circumstances, Sahm Capital may need to utilise Third-Party Service to support the Services or provide certain services upon the request of the User.  The User acknowledges that in case of accessing or using a Third-Party Service, the User shall refer to and agree to be bound by the applicable terms of use and privacy policy of such third party. To the extent possible and in line with the relevant rules and regulations, Sahm Capital will protect the data and privacy of the User from infringement through the implementation of relevant agreements entered with Third Party Service provider(s). However, under no circumstances does Sahm Capital guarantee the security, accuracy or effectiveness of the products or services provided by any Third-Party Service provider. Sahm Capital also does not guarantee that the User will not be exposed to other potential risks when using the products or services of a Third-Party Service provider. By using a Third-Party Service provider, the User agrees to assume all risk and liability arising from such usage. The User shall be solely responsible for the relevant consequences and liabilities and Sahm Capital shall not assume any responsibility whatsoever.
In utilizing any information service provided by the information providers, users hereby acknowledge and commit to abiding by the following conditions:
a. Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq and other Information Providers reserve all intellectual Property Rights to the information.
b. Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq and other Information Providers accept no liability for the display of the Information or any losses or claims arising from use of the Information.
c. Information is for the personal use of the recipient and may not be redistributed by the recipient to any third party without the permission of Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq, and other Information Providers.
d. Recipients have no right to use Information in Automated Trading Applications, to create Derived Data or to process Information, with or without other data, for the purpose of creating Indices, or to license any third party to create Indices, without the prior written permission of Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq, and other Information Providers.
e. Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq and other Information Providers may suspend or terminate receipt of Information by any party if Saudi Exchange, Nasdaq, and other Information Providers have reason to believe the Information is being misused or misrepresented.
5. User Privacy Protection
Sahm Capital respects and protects the privacy of the User. Sahm Capital will protect the personal privacy of the User strictly in accordance with the requirements of relevant laws and regulations. Please refer to the Privacy Policy for more details about the protection of the personal data of the users.
