Unless explicitly specified herein, the software, logos, trademarks, structures and designs of the Services, pictures, videos, information, market data, files and other related materials presented or used on the Services or provided by Sahm Capital shall be the proprietary property of Sahm Capital or licensors of Sahm Capital. No rights to such Services (in part or in full), regardless of the form, are conveyed to the User by using or accessing the Services nor shall such constitute an assignment of any rights.
Subject to compliance by the User with these terms of the Agreement, the User is granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-sublicensable, non-assignable, non-transferable and revocable license to access and use the Services as they relate to the User personally, including but not limited to downloading or installing the APP on the mobile phone of the User, install the client software on a personal computer or view the market data provided that such use shall be exclusively for non-commercial purposes and always subject to the Undertakings.
Without prior written approval of Sahm Capital and relevant right holders, such license does not include:
a. any resale or commercial use of the Services.
b. modifying, archiving, copying, reproducing, distributing, publishing, transmitting, translating or otherwise making any derivative uses of the Services or any portion thereof, unless expressly permitted under applicable law or the Agreement.
c. reverse compiling the Services or extracting the essential parts of the Services for other application.
d. use of any data mining, robots or similar data gathering or extraction methods to intended to extract data or information from the Services.
e. makes use of the aforesaid information and content to charge any improper fees from any other person.
f. any use of the Services other than for their intended purposes.  Any unauthorised use of the Services is strictly prohibited and Sahm Capital will terminate the license granted herein at its sole discretion upon a perceived breach of the terms of the Agreement.
Such unauthorised use may also violate the applicable laws, including without limitation copyright and trademark laws and the rules of the CMA. The User shall be solely responsible for any unauthorised use of the Services and hereby assumes all liabilities thus incurred.
7. Risk Disclosure
The content and information provided by Sahm Capital are analysed and interpreted based on publicly available information collected from public sources or is posted or provided by other users, partners or other third parties. Sahm Capital will endeavour to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the content and information provided, however, Sahm Capital cannot and does not guarantee its absolute accuracy and reliability and shall not be liable for any loss or damage (whether tort or contractual or otherwise) arising out of any inaccuracies or omissions. The User should consult its own personal advisors regarding such information. The User acknowledges and agrees that the User shall judge the accuracy of such content and information, which shall only be used for reference and guidance.
Access or use of any service platform or pages of Sahm Capital by the User to obtain relevant services or carry out relevant operation with reference to the content or information provided by Sahm Capital shall be at the sole risk and loss of the User. Sahm Capital shall not bear any liabilities of breach, infringement or any other civil responsibilities for the risks or losses that are incurred by the User pursuant to the conduct of the User.
Under no circumstances should the User trust any information about borrowing money, requesting a password or other property. The User should be independent, sober, and objective about the aforementioned information and be cautious about fraud and only trust information that in the sole discretion of the User is credible and from a reliable source and in consultation with its personal advisors.
