9. Limitation of Liability
in no event shall sahm capital be liable for any damages, losses or liabilities including without limitation, direct or indirect, special, incidental, consequential damages, losses or liabilities, including, but not limited to, loss of use, loss of profits or loss of data, whether in an action in contract, tort (including, but not limited to, negligence) or otherwise, arising out of or in connection with the use of the services by the user or your reliance on or use or inability to use the information, materials, products through the services provided by sahm capital, or in connection with any failure of performance, error, omission, interruption, defect, delay in operation or transmission, computer virus or line or system failure, even if you advise us of the possibility of such damages, losses or expenses.
10. Applicable Laws and Jurisdiction
The execution, effectiveness, performance, termination, and dispute settlement of the Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.
Any dispute arising in the execution, effectiveness, performance, and termination of the Agreement, Sahm Capital expects to settle through friendly consultation with the User. In the event, the consultation fails, or the result of the consultation is not satisfactory to the Parties, either the User or Sahm Capital shall have the right to file a lawsuit wherein jurisdiction to resolve such dispute shall be with the courts of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, in Riyadh. at the sole discretion and for the benefit of Sahm Capital.
At the sole discretion and for the benefit of Sahm Capital, a dispute or proceeding may be commenced by Sahm Capital with the Committee for Resolution of Securities Disputes (the CRSD) in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.
11. Termination
The Agreement shall be terminated in the event:
a. The User closes the Account, discontinues use of the Services, and provides Sahm Capital with a written notice of termination.
b. The User does not accept a modification or amendment of the terms of the Agreement, uninstalls the Services or no longer uses the product and relevant services as confirmed in writing to Sahm Capital by the User.
c. The User violates the Agreement wherein Sahm Capital shall be entitled to terminate the Agreement immediately without notice and terminate the rights of the User to use the Services or any portion thereof, and to block or prevent future access by the User to the Services without assuming any liabilities of the breach.
d. A Force Majeure event occurs and results in the impossibility to perform the Agreement or continue to provide the Services wherein the User or Sahm Capital shall have the right to terminate the Agreement and Services without assuming any liabilities of the breach.
In case of termination of the Agreement, regardless of the reasons, the qualification of the User shall become invalid upon the date of such termination and the right of the User to use the Services shall immediately cease. The User acknowledges and agrees that it shall immediately deactivate or uninstall the APP and all related information and files on its device and shall not attempt any further access to such files or the Services, and Sahm Capital shall not be liable to the User or any third party for any claims or damages arising out of any termination or in connection with such termination.
12. Miscellaneous
Assignment
The User may not assign its rights or obligations under this Agreement without the prior written consent of Sahm Capital. Sahm Capital may assign any or all its rights under this Agreement, in whole or in part, and the User consents to such approval and agrees and confirms that no further consent or approval of the User shall be required for such assignment or transfer, nor shall any formal notice of such consent or transfer be required to the User.
Waiver
The failure or delay of Sahm Capital in exercising any right, power or privilege under the Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver thereof.
Severability
If any term of the Agreement is deemed unlawful, void, or unenforceable for any reason, such term shall not affect the validity or enforceability of any other term of the Agreement, all of which shall remain in full force and effect.
Survival
Article 6 (Intellectual Property), 8 (Disclaimer), 9 (Limitation of Liability), 10 (Applicable Laws and Jurisdiction), and 11 (Termination) will survive any termination of this Agreement or use of the Services.
13. The language of the Agreement
This agreement has been executed into the Arabic language, and in case that it is translated into the English language, the Arabic language text shall prevail against the text of any other language.
